  "text": "Note added in proof. At the time this manuscript was submitted for publication Olefsky [CITATION_1] reported decreased insulin binding to fat cells and circulating monocytes from obese subjects. Decreased binding was present only in those subjects with hyperinsulinemia. There was a significant inverse correlation between the fasting plasma insulin level and fat cell insulin binding. The present study confirms this relationship and also shows that binding, in particular receptor number, is closely correlated with a direct index of tissue insulin sensitivity, the Kin.",
